The '''American Osteopathic Board of Preventive Medicine''' ('''AOBPM''') is an organization that provides [[board certification]] to qualified [[Doctor of Osteopathic Medicine|Doctors of Osteopathic Medicine]] (D.O.) who specialize in aiding patients in the prevention of injury or disease ([[Preventive medicine|preventive medicine physicians]]). The board is one of 18 physician [[Specialty (medicine)|medical specialty]] boards of the [[American Osteopathic Association Bureau of Osteopathic Specialists]] of the [[American Osteopathic Association]] (AOA).<ref>{{cite web|title=American Osteopathic Board of Preventive Medicine (AOBPM)|url=http://www.hwic.org/experts/details.php?id=3125|publisher=Health Workforce Information Center|accessdate=26 August 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.osteopathic.org/inside-aoa/development/aoa-board-certification/Pages/aoa-specialty-boards.aspx/ |title=AOA Specialty Certifying Boards |publisher=Osteopathic.org |date= |accessdate=2012-08-26}}</ref><ref>[http://www.osteopathic.org/inside-aoa/development/aoa-board-certification/Documents/bos-handbook.pdf/ Handbook of Procedures of the Bureau of Osteopathic Specialists, July 2010.]</ref> The AOBPM was established in 1982 by approval by the Board of Trustees of the American Osteopathic Association. The AOBPM provides [[board certification]] for eligible physicians. Additionally, along with fellows of the [[American Board of Preventive Medicine]], fellows of the American Osteopathic Board of Preventive Medicine are eligible to become fellows of the [[Undersea and Hyperbaric Medical Society]].<ref>{{cite web|title=UHM Fellow|url=http://membership.uhms.org/?page=UHM_Fellow|publisher=Undersea and Hyperbaric Medical Society|year=2011|accessdate=17 September 2012}}</ref> As of December 2011, 176 [[Osteopathic medicine in the United States|osteopathic]] physicians held active membership with the AOBPM.<ref>{{cite journal|last=Ayres|first=Ronald E|coauthors=S Scheinthal, C Gross, and E Bell.|title=Changes to Osteopathic Specialty Board Certification|journal=Journal of the American Osteopathic Association|year=2012|month=April|volume=112|issue=4|pages=226–231|url=http://www.jaoa.org/content/112/4/226.full.pdf+html|accessdate=26 August 2012}}</ref>

==Board certification==
The AOBPM is responsible for evaluation and recommendation for [[Osteopathic medicine in the United States|osteopathic]] medical board certification in the specialty areas of [[Aerospace Medicine]]/Undersea & [[Hyperbaric Medicine]], [[Occupational medicine|Occupational & Environmental Medicine]], and [[Public Health]] & General Preventive Medicine.<ref name=Specialties /><ref>{{cite web|title=Preventive Medicine|url=http://medicine.nova.edu/do/departments/preventive.html|publisher=Nova Southeastern University College of Osteopathic Medicine|year=2008|accessdate=17 September 2012}}</ref>  Additionally, the AOBPM is responsible for the certificate of added qualifications (CAQ) in Occupational Medicine, and Undersea & Hyperbaric Medicine.<ref name=Specialties>{{cite web|title=Specialties & Subspecialties|url=http://www.osteopathic.org/inside-aoa/development/aoa-board-certification/Pages/specialty-subspecialty-certification.aspx|publisher=American Osteopathic Association|accessdate=26 August 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Medical Boards: Osteopathic|url=http://www.castleconnolly.com/resources/osteopathic.cfm|publisher=Castle Connolly Medical,Ltd.|accessdate=17 September 2012}}</ref>

Osteopathic physicians may enter an AOA-accredited or [[Accreditation Council for Graduate Medical Education|ACGME]]-accredited Preventive Medicine residency program. Osteopathic physicians from both pathways are eligible for board certification through the AOBPM.<ref>{{cite web|title=Certification|url=http://www.aobpm.org/Certification.html|publisher=American Osteopathic Board of Preventive Medicine |accessdate= 21 April 2013}}</ref>

AOBPM General Certification, Recertification and Certificate of Added Qualifications examinations are offered annually, every spring, in conjunction with the [[American Osteopathic College of Occupational & Preventive Medicine]] Mid-Year Educational Conference.

